nal Justice and Public Order Act 1994 be amended to remove the conditions in subsection (1)—namely conditions (a) and (b) and the conditions of ‘two or more persons’, ‘reasonable steps have been by or on behalf of the occupier to ask them to leave’—in order to make it an offence for a trespasser to fail to comply with a direction by police to leave land and remove vehicles or property, as in Section 24 of the Housing (Miscellaneous Provisions) Act 2002, an Act of the Parliament of the Republic of Ireland. And your Petitioners, as in duty bound, will ever pray, &c. [P002152]     Share                   ×   Suggest Correction            Your Details:         Enter your suggested correction:   0 /1000          Please prove you are not a robot.        Close  Submit               A-Z index | Glossary | Contact us | Freedom of Information | Data Protection |  Jobs | Using this website |  Copyright     © Parliamentary Copyright                     Cookies: We use cookies to give you the best possible experience on our site. By continuing to use the site you
